class Solution {
    public String getHint(String secret, String guess) {
        int[] countSecret = new int[10];
        int[] countGuess = new int[10];
        int bulls = 0;
        for (int i = 0; i < secret.length(); i++) {
            char s = secret.charAt(i);
            char g = guess.charAt(i);
            if (s == g) {
                bulls++;
            } else {
                countSecret[s - '0']++;
                countGuess[g - '0']++;
            }
        }
        int cows = 0;
        for (int i = 0; i < 10; i++) {
            cows += Math.min(countSecret[i], countGuess[i]);
        }
        return bulls + "A" + cows + "B";
    }
}
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution iterates through the secret and guess strings once, counting bulls and storing counts of non-bull digits in arrays. It then calculates cows by summing the minimum counts for each digit. This approach efficiently handles duplicate digits and has a linear time complexity.
